    "updated_at": "2015-10-28T21:04:30Z",
    "body": "@paulcbetts I see, I am asking because there seems to be API on Mac to detect if an application with a specific bundle id is already running:\n\nhttp://stackoverflow.com/questions/8249686/launchapplication-with-command-line-arguments\nhttp://blog.jseibert.com/post/1167439217/deduplicating-running-instances-or-how-to-detect\n\nMy feeling is that the decision to make an app a singleton instance should not be made in the code that I write in my main.js file but rather something that has to run as early as possible even before my code is reached. This would also bring down the time it takes to spawn the second instance even further.\n\nWith the current solution I still briefly see the Mac dock bounce with the second instance launching and then disappear. Idealy this would not happen.\n"
  },
