    "created_at": "2015-10-28T21:19:11Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-28T21:19:11Z",
    "body": "> My feeling is that the decision to make an app a singleton instance should not be made in the code that I write in my main.js file but rather something that has to run as early as possible even before my code is reached.\n\nThis means that the app can't choose to ignore singleton instance which means that things like Squirrel hooks will be blocked by single instance\n\n> With the current solution I still briefly see the Mac dock bounce with the second instance launching and then disappear. Idealy this would not happen.\n\nHow early are you calling `makeSingleInstance`? You can call it very very early (pre-ready). \n"
